  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "Despite extensive U.S. and Israeli airstrikes on Iran since February 28, 2026—including operations targeting nuclear sites, military capabilities, and mines in the Strait of Hormuz—President Trump has avoided a formal war declaration, referring to the conflict informally as \"war\" without unambiguous language like \"the United States is now at war with Iran.\" A Pakistan-mediated ceasefire took effect April 8 and was extended indefinitely April 21, amid negotiations and Trump's mixed signals on escalation versus de-escalation, with core objectives reportedly nearing completion. Low trader consensus for an April 30 declaration reflects this trajectory, though fragile talks, Senate war powers debates, and a potential May 1 deadline for military actions could prompt shifts.",
    "context_requires_regen": false,
